<|> 𝐑𝐚𝐧𝐠𝐞𝐬 𝐨𝐟 𝐃𝐚𝐭𝐚 𝐓𝐲𝐩𝐞𝐬 <|>
____________________________________________________________________
|   𝐃𝐚𝐭𝐚 𝐓𝐲𝐩𝐞 |><|     𝐒𝐢𝐳𝐞     |><|       𝐑𝐚𝐧𝐠𝐞                    |
|"""""""""""""""|""""""""""""""""|""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""|
|     byte      |    8 - Bit     |  -128 to 127                     |
|---------------|----------------|----------------------------------|
|     short     |   16 - Bit     |  -32,768 to 32,767               |
|---------------|----------------|----------------------------------\
|     int       |   32 - Bit     |  -2,147,483,648 to 2,147,483,647  \
|---------------|----------------|------------------------------------\--------------|
|     long      |   64 - Bit     |  -9,223,372,036,854,775,808 to + Same to last 807 |
|---------------|----------------|------------------------------------/--------------|
|     float     |   32 - Bit     |  ±3.40282347E+38                  /
|---------------|----------------|----------------------------------/
|     double    |   64 - Bit     |  ±1.79769313486231570E+308      |
|---------------|----------------|---------------------------------|          |
|'''''''''''''''|''''''''''''''''|'''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''|
|     char      |   16 - Bit     | A - Z , a - z , 0 to 65,535 , @ |
|---------------|----------------|---------------------------------|
|    boolean    |    1 - Bit     |  " true " or " false "          |
|_______________|________________|_________________________________|


>> The value given in table are correct, so all code are executed without error.
>> But, all data type have their own limitation value from minimum to maximum.
>> If your input is out from min & max value , you got Error in code.
>> You can code only in ranges of data types to execute the correct code.

----------------------><---------------------------><-----------------------------

E᙭ᗩᗰᑭᒪE
𝑪𝒐𝒅𝒆 𝒇𝒐𝒓 𝒃𝒚𝒕𝒆 -->>
   class Main
   {
     public static void main(String []args)
     {
       byte x = -128;
       byte y = 127;

       System.out.println(x);
       System.out.println(y);
     }
   }
You can try & check with out of ranges to get error.
     byte x = -130
     byte y = 129

𝑪𝒐𝒅𝒆 𝒇𝒐𝒓 𝒊𝒏𝒕 -->>
   class Main
   {
     public static void main(String []args)
     {
       int x = -2,147,483,648;  //code without comma
       int y = 2,147,483,647;

       System.out.println(x);
       System.out.println(y);
     }
   }
You can try & check with out of ranges to get error.
     int x = -2,147,483,700
     int y = 2,147,483,800

